Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina State, has approved the dissolution of Chairmen and members of the State Boards of Parastatals with immediate effect. In a statement by Mustapha Muhammed Inuwa, the Secretary to the Government of the State, disclosed this in Katsina, saying the dissolution followed the expiration of the first dispensetion on which they were appointed to serve. According to him, “Those affected were all Chairmen and members who appointments were not on tenure system” He added that their disengagement is to pave way for the reconstruction of new board members in line with the dictates of next level agenda of the APC-led administration in the state. The governor appreciated the Chairmen and members of the State Board of Parastatals for their immeasurable contributions to the success of the last tenure, wishing them success in their future endeavours.